                    <name>richTextValue</name>
                    <value>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Capability Binding: JSON Guidance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Configure how &lt;em&gt;this specific Agent&lt;/em&gt; uses the linked Action.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Action Implementation Configuration (JSON Data - Optional)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose:&lt;/strong&gt; Provide specific &lt;em&gt;backend configuration data&lt;/em&gt; (not schema) to the linked Action&apos;s logic (Apex/Flow), overriding defaults if applicable.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Format:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Must match the Binding Config Schema defined on the selected &apos;Action Implementation Logic&apos; (Action Definition record).&lt;/strong&gt; Typically a JSON Map like {&quot;key&quot;: &quot;value&quot;}.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check First:&lt;/strong&gt; Review the Binding Config Schema on the Action Definition to see what data structure is expected here.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; (If Action Definition schema required targetRecordTypeApiName)&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;{&quot;targetRecordTypeApiName&quot;: &quot;Opportunity_Large_Deal&quot;}&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leave Blank:&lt;/strong&gt; If the linked Action doesn&apos;t require specific backend settings for this binding, or if defaults are acceptable.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Capability Input Schema (JSON Schema for Agent/LLM)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Defines arguments the &lt;em&gt;Agent/LLM MUST provide&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; when invoking &lt;em&gt;this specific capability&lt;/em&gt; (using this binding&apos;s Developer Name). Presented to the LLM.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Format:&lt;/strong&gt; Standard JSON Schema {&quot;type&quot;: &quot;object&quot;, ...} like OpenAI functions. Define properties and required arguments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consistency is Key:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;This schema should generally be identical to the LLM Input Parameter Schema on the linked &apos;Action Implementation Logic&apos; (Action Definition)&lt;/strong&gt; to avoid confusion and ensure the LLM provides the correct arguments needed by the backend logic. Copy/paste from the Action Definition is recommended.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; (Mirroring the Action Definition&apos;s schema)&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;object&quot;, &quot;properties&quot;: {&quot;recordId&quot;: {&quot;type&quot;: &quot;string&quot;, &quot;description&quot;: &quot;The Salesforce ID&quot;}, &quot;comment&quot;: {&quot;type&quot;: &quot;string&quot;}}, &quot;required&quot;: [&quot;recordId&quot;]}&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No Params?:&lt;/strong&gt; Use {&quot;type&quot;: &quot;object&quot;, &quot;properties&quot;: {}}.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</value>
